      • isGroupAttribute

        public boolean isGroupAttribute​(java.lang.String appName,
                                java.lang.String attrName)
                         throws GeneralException
        Is the given attribute a group attribute on the given application. Note: This will only test for directly assignable group attributes. (attributes on the account schema) It is possible to have a group attribute on a group schema instead of the account schema.
        Parameters:
        appName - The application on which the attribute lives.
        attrName - The name of the attribute to check.
        Returns:
        True if the given attribute on the given application is a "group" attribute, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        GeneralException

      • isGroupAttribute

        public boolean isGroupAttribute​(java.lang.String appName,
                                java.lang.String attrName,
                                java.lang.String schemaName)
                         throws GeneralException
        Is the given attribute a group attribute on the given application and schema.
        Parameters:
        appName - The application on which the attribute lives.
        attrName - The name of the attribute to check.
        schemaName - The optional schema name, this method will look here if the group is not found in Account schema.
        Returns:
        True if the given attribute on the given application is a "group" attribute, false otherwise.

        GeneralException

      • getAccountGroup

        public ManagedAttribute getAccountGroup​(java.lang.String appName,
                                        java.lang.String groupAttr,
                                        java.lang.String groupVal)
                                 throws GeneralException
        Return the ManagedAttribute (if one exists) for a given group on an application.
        Parameters:
        appName - The name of the Application on which the group lives.
        groupAttr - The name of the attribute on the Application that is a "group" attribute (eg - memberOf).
        groupVal - The system name of the group (eg - cn=MyGroup,dc=blah).
        Returns:
        The ManagedAttribute for a given group on an application, or null if an ManagedAttribute does not exist with the given attributes.
        Throws:
        GeneralException

                                         throws GeneralException
        Return the displayable name of the ManagedAttribute (if one exists) for a given group on an application.
        Parameters:
        appName - The name of the Application on which the group lives.
        attr - The name of the attribute on the Application that is a "group" attribute (eg: memberOf).
        val - The system name of the group (eg: cn=MyGroup,dc=blah).
        Returns:

        GeneralException

      • getGroupDisplayableNames

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getGroupDisplayableNames​(java.lang.String appName,
                                                                 java.lang.String attr,
                                                                 java.lang.Object vals)
                                                          throws GeneralException
        Return the displayable name(s) of the AccountGroup (if one exists) for a given group on an application. The incoming values might be a single String or a List of Strings, depending on the attribute.
        Parameters:
        appName - The name of the Application on which the group lives.
        attr - The name of the attribute on the Application that is a "group" attribute (eg: memberOf).
        vals - The system name(s) of the group (eg: cn=MyGroup,dc=blah).
        Returns:
        A list of the displayable names of the AccountGroup, or the attr values if an AccountGroup does not exist with the given attributes.
        Throws:
        GeneralException

      • getMemberNames

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getMemberNames​(ManagedAttribute group,
                                                       java.lang.String memberNameAttribute)
                                                throws GeneralException
        Return a list of members for a given account group. This method uses extended multivalued attributes to resolve group membership if the memberAttribute is not null on the account group. Otherwise starting in 6.0, it uses the IdentityEntitlement relationship to compute the relationships. Note: Indirectly Assignable Acount groups will not have an attribute set.
        Throws:
        GeneralException
